post_text: Superintendent's Report 8/4/20
text: Superintendent's Report 8/4/20

post_text:
Dear Parents and Guardians,

I hope that you are all having a safe summer. Almost 90% of families filled out our last survey, which helped us begin planning for September. However, we know that information and circumstances are fluid and changing each and everyday. As we continue to make preparations for the 2020-21 school year, ALL families must log on to the parent portal and answer a brief question regarding your choice of virtual or in school learning for each child.

While we understand that families may struggle with a final decision at this moment, it is crucial that we have an accurate snapshot of enrollment to plan for the safe reopening of our school. You can review a draft of our reopening plan on our website before making your decision. THIS MUST BE COMPLETED BY Friday, August 7th.

As always, please reach out should you have any questions or concerns.

Your partner in all of this,
Principal DeLaura

post_text:
July 30, 2020

Dear Norwood Families:

I am writing to inform you that there is a proposal to change the date for the first day of school to allow teachers additional time for preparation. The new date proposed is September 3rd, which is one day later than what is listed on the school calendar. The Norwood BOE is expected to consider the recommendation at our next BOE meeting which is scheduled for August 18th. Please note, however, new information is being released every day and plans continue to remain fluid. As additional guidelines from the NJDOE are released, we will make sure to share it with you.

Finally, if you haven’t already completed the survey, please do so tonight. The survey will only be open until tomorrow. Thank you for your assistance.

Sincerely,
Lisa Gross
Superintendent

post_text:
PreK- 4 Supply Pick Up
In order to avoid a long line/ wait, please spread out your arrival time between your scheduled hour.
(ie: 9:15, 9:30.9:45)
Dear Parents and Guardians,

We are in the process of making arrangements for our students and families to retrieve the contents from their classrooms. Each classroom in Grades PK-4 has been emptied into a bag and labeled with the student name. We ask that you drive up to the circle with a sign that reads with your last name and your grade/ section (For example: DeLaura last name 2-D grade/ section). Please do not get out of your car, someone will be available to assist you.
See the times below:

Pre K-K 8:30- 9:30
Grade 1 9:30-10:30
Grade 2 10:30- 11:30
Grade 3 11:30-12:00
Grade 4 12:00-1:00

If you are unable to make the scheduled time, please let us know and we will make accommodations. We look forward to "seeing" you on Wednesday, June 10th.

Hello Norwood Community, we are looking to create an uplifting and inspiring video for our students. We are asking for NPS graduates and alumni to create a 30 second video sharing something positive they learned while at Norwood Public School as a way of encouraging our students to continue to be engaged learners during this difficult time. The video can include your name, class year, special memories, skills or lessons learned, and well wishes to our students and faculty. Please send all mp4 files to gulkoa@nvnet.org.
Thank you for your support!

post_text: Our 7th and 8th Grade Peer Leaders read The Giving Tree by Shel Silverstein to 2nd grade classes. Students then did a small writing activity. Each student wrote what they are most grateful for on cut out leaves. The Peer Leaders will display the leaves on a big bulletin board. The students enjoyed their lesson and some of our Peer Leaders may have found their calling!

post_text: This year the Norwood Community contributed about 60 backpacks filled with essential items and messages of hope to the JL Blessings Backpack Initiative. JL Blessings was able to distribute 1,144 filled backpacks to the less fortunate in New York City and Newark. The recipients were filled with emotion and gratitude for the kindness and generosity shared with them by strangers. Thank you to everyone that participated in this event to make a positive difference in someone's life!
